      "span_text": "Recent advances in low-switching-voltage nematic LC materials and layer thickness control have allowed the incorporation of a thin quarterwave-plate (QWP) layer between the LC and the aluminium mirror to accomplish polarization-insensitive multi-phase-level Opto-VLSI processors"
